ence time exceeds 5 minutes, consider using a single, larger, well-regularized CNF and using "Monte Carlo Dropout" at test time to generate the `errorbars` instead of a full ensemble. This reduces the memory overhead and loading time significantly.\n\n6. **Normalization of Scores**: In Step 7, instead of a simple 5th-percentile mapping, consider using a Z-score approach relative to the validation set mean and standard deviation. This is more robust to outliers and provides a more stable input for the partial AUC calculation.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='a9dd78cf-408e-43b4-a23a-79318656870e'



